radiographic_examinations.findings: Bilateral dependent atelectasis in lung bases, no concerning nodules, lesions or pleural effusions. Dilated appendix measuring up to 13 mm with surrounding fat stranding, adjacent sigmoid bowel wall thickening likely reactive, diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon, incidental duplicated inferior vena cava and retroaortic left renal vein, no free air, free fluid or pathologically enlarged lymph nodes.
